00:01:06.960 --> 00:01:10.350
Just to give you Shalva
101 for two minutes.

00:01:10.350 --> 00:01:13.470
I'm a Canadian from
Vancouver, Canada.

00:01:13.470 --> 00:01:17.220
Went to Israel when I was
18 on my way to France.

00:01:17.220 --> 00:01:21.570
Stayed, became religious,
and my beautiful wife, Malki,

00:01:21.570 --> 00:01:27.480
and our second child, Yossi,
at the age of 11 months

00:01:27.480 --> 00:01:30.750
had a medical issue that
developed and-- well not--

00:01:30.750 --> 00:01:32.400
let's say that again.

00:01:32.400 --> 00:01:35.400
There was a medical
procedure that went bad,

00:01:35.400 --> 00:01:38.100
and he became blind and deaf.

00:01:38.100 --> 00:01:40.740
And people asked my wife to
think about putting him out

00:01:40.740 --> 00:01:44.220
of the house because he
was very, very challenging.

00:01:44.220 --> 00:01:46.784
And my wife would
cry at night and say,

00:01:46.784 --> 00:01:48.700
God I am never putting
Yossi out of the house.

00:01:48.700 --> 00:01:51.180
But if you ever decide
to help our Yossi,

00:01:51.180 --> 00:01:53.820
I'm going to dedicate my
life to helping other mothers

00:01:53.820 --> 00:01:56.160
with their challenges.

00:01:56.160 --> 00:02:00.150
At the age of eight,
unexpected, Yossi

00:02:00.150 --> 00:02:04.680
had a breakthrough to
communication via a teacher

00:02:04.680 --> 00:02:08.669
in the deaf school who was
deaf herself, and spelling

00:02:08.669 --> 00:02:10.949
the word of palm of his
hand over and over again,

00:02:10.949 --> 00:02:13.080
the five Hebrew letters
for the word table

00:02:13.080 --> 00:02:14.640
or [SPEAKING HEBREW].

00:02:14.640 --> 00:02:18.180
Yossi suddenly lit up, and
she, in her words, said,

00:02:18.180 --> 00:02:21.480
he just had his
Helen Keller moment.

00:02:21.480 --> 00:02:22.774
So she turned to me.

00:02:22.774 --> 00:02:23.940
She said, it's payback time.

00:02:23.940 --> 00:02:25.850
I know exactly
what I want to do.

00:02:25.850 --> 00:02:27.600
I know how you want
to help other mothers.

00:02:27.600 --> 00:02:29.880
It took me three
years to find anyone

00:02:29.880 --> 00:02:32.880
who would buy into her dream.

00:02:32.880 --> 00:02:37.060
We opened with five children
with cognitive disabilities.

00:02:37.060 --> 00:02:39.390
Malki did everything
except for a professional

00:02:39.390 --> 00:02:41.350
and a few volunteers.

00:02:41.350 --> 00:02:44.970
And it grew in ways that we
could never have foreseen.

00:02:44.970 --> 00:02:51.520
Today, we serve over 2000
people a week from birth,

00:02:51.520 --> 00:02:54.180
including mothers
who just gave birth

00:02:54.180 --> 00:02:56.250
to babies they
weren't expecting,

00:02:56.250 --> 00:02:58.650
and all the way through
to independent living

00:02:58.650 --> 00:03:02.210
in the community and seniors.

00:03:02.210 --> 00:03:07.110
The band is yet
another dream that we

00:03:07.110 --> 00:03:11.130
began 11 years ago
and no one could have

00:03:11.130 --> 00:03:14.220
expected where they have come.

00:03:14.220 --> 00:03:16.180
These are young adults.

00:03:16.180 --> 00:03:18.480
These people have the
respect of now making

00:03:18.480 --> 00:03:20.970
a living through their music.

00:03:20.970 --> 00:03:24.660
